I had these bruises on my arms.

573
00:35:35,433 --> 00:35:36,467
And?

574
00:35:36,567 --> 00:35:38,469
I wondered how I got them.

575
00:35:38,569 --> 00:35:41,472
Mrs. Noel, sometimes
you flail your arms

576
00:35:41,572 --> 00:35:44,375
during the amytal interview
and I have to restrain you.

577
00:35:44,475 --> 00:35:45,343
I'm sorry if you're bruised.

578
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:47,812
You bruise easily, huh?

579
00:35:47,912 --> 00:35:49,714
Yes.

580
00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:52,116
But I even have a
bruise on my pubic bone.

581
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:55,520
How did I get that?

582
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:57,388
How dare you.

583
00:35:57,488 --> 00:36:00,658
How dare you occupy my time with
these silly trivial concerns.

584
00:36:00,758 --> 00:36:03,861
How and where you bruise
is of no concern to me.

585
00:36:03,961 --> 00:36:05,596
And if you ever raise
your voice to me again,

586
00:36:05,696 --> 00:36:07,598
you'll never get
another drop of amytal.

587
00:36:07,698 --> 00:36:11,135
You understand me, Mrs. Noel?

588
00:36:11,235 --> 00:36:13,704
What were you
afraid of, Barbara?

589
00:36:13,804 --> 00:36:15,540
Learning the truth?

590
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,942
Or getting cut off from amytal?

591
00:36:18,042 --> 00:36:19,911
You keep saying that, but
I'm not addicted to amytal.

592
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:20,811
How could I be?

593
00:36:20,912 --> 00:36:22,079
I haven't had any in weeks.

594
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:24,115
No, you're drinking.

595
00:36:24,215 --> 00:36:27,185
You're drinking gin, am I right?

596
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:29,487
Gin is the closest
thing to an amytal high.

597
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:36,294
Barbara, I know how difficult
it is for you to trust again,

598
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:38,896
but I need you to trust me.

599
00:36:38,996 --> 00:36:41,199
You may have much
deeper problems.

600
00:36:41,299 --> 00:36:43,401
And I think that
we can get to them

601
00:36:43,501 --> 00:36:45,169
by meeting on a regular basis.

602
00:36:45,269 --> 00:36:48,105
And then maybe someday
when you're ready,

603
00:36:48,206 --> 00:36:50,308
I would like to try
hypnosis with you.

604
00:36:50,408 --> 00:36:51,943
Hypnosis, why hypnosis?

605
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:56,080
I think it would help us, help
us uncover something important

606
00:36:56,180 --> 00:36:58,416
since Dr. Masserman
never revealed what came

607
00:36:58,516 --> 00:36:59,617
out of the amytal sessions.

608
00:37:10,628 --> 00:37:12,997
Mr. Flynn, hi.

609
00:37:13,097 --> 00:37:15,533
You wanted to see me.

610
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:19,704
Yes, Barbara, I did.

611
00:37:19,804 --> 00:37:23,074
This is Masserman's resume.

612
00:37:23,174 --> 00:37:25,576
It's 30 pages long.

613
00:37:25,676 --> 00:37:29,146
It lists his awards, all
the books he's written,

614
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:32,216
president of this,
president of that for life.

615
00:37:32,316 --> 00:37:33,884
You sound surprised.

616
00:37:33,985 --> 00:37:36,020
You knew how important he is.

617
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,588
Important?

618
00:37:37,688 --> 00:37:40,524
Barbara, this man
is beyond important.

619
00:37:40,625 --> 00:37:43,527
I mean, he's a
giant in his field.

620
00:37:43,628 --> 00:37:45,696
Look, I've talked to all
kinds of psychiatrists.

621
00:37:45,796 --> 00:37:49,033
No one is willing to
testify against Masserman.

622
00:37:49,133 --> 00:37:51,902
It's down to your
word against his.

623
00:37:52,003 --> 00:37:54,038
And the bottom line is--

624
00:37:54,138 --> 00:37:56,207
the bottom line is I
can't win this case.

625
00:37:56,307 --> 00:37:57,275
I'm going to have to withdraw.

626
00:37:57,375 --> 00:37:58,175
But you can't.

627
00:37:58,276 --> 00:38:00,011
You already filed the complaint.

628
00:38:00,077 --> 00:38:03,281
I'm sorry, but I didn't get
in this business to suffer

629
00:38:03,381 --> 00:38:05,583
personal embarrassment.

630
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:07,585
And you, according
to this letter

631
00:38:07,685 --> 00:38:10,454
that I received from
Masserman's attorney,

632
00:38:10,554 --> 00:38:11,989
are a very troubled person.

633
00:38:12,089 --> 00:38:17,428
Barbara, it's Masserman's expert
opinion that you're unstable.

634
00:38:17,528 --> 00:38:18,863
They got to you, didn't they?

635
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:25,269
You have three weeks
to find a new attorney

636
00:38:25,369 --> 00:38:27,905
or the court will
dismiss the complaint.

637
00:38:28,005 --> 00:38:30,941
You want my advice,
Barbara, give it up.

638
00:38:31,042 --> 00:38:34,111
You're not believable.

639
00:38:34,211 --> 00:38:35,112
They'll cut you to pieces.

640
00:38:38,749 --> 00:38:39,917
Good day, Mr. Flynn.

641
00:38:53,397 --> 00:38:58,569
(SINGING) But for
tonight, forget it.

642
00:38:58,669 --> 00:39:06,711
I'm in the mood for love.

643
00:39:16,654 --> 00:39:18,255
Barbara Noel,
ladies and gentlemen.

644
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:19,390
We're going to
take a short break.

645
00:39:19,490 --> 00:39:20,391
We'll be right back.

646
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,461
Be right there.

647
00:39:33,471 --> 00:39:35,339
I'll pick up in the next set.

648
00:39:35,439 --> 00:39:37,508
If there is a next set.

649
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:38,576
It's not the drinking.

650
00:39:38,676 --> 00:39:41,379
I'm under a lot of pressure.

651
00:39:41,479 --> 00:39:44,215
Yeah.

652
00:39:44,315 --> 00:39:47,418
Well, me too, pressure
from the guys.

653
00:39:47,518 --> 00:39:48,486
They're getting fed up.

654
00:39:48,586 --> 00:39:49,754
There's not enough gigs.

655
00:39:49,854 --> 00:39:51,389
We're losing ones we've
always been able to count on.

656
00:39:51,489 --> 00:39:52,423
They're not happy, Barbara.

657
00:39:52,523 --> 00:39:54,058
Neither am I.
- What are you saying?

658
00:39:54,158 --> 00:39:55,226
I'm fired?
You want to fire me?

659
00:39:55,326 --> 00:39:56,160
Is that it?

660
00:39:56,260 --> 00:39:58,028
What the hell is
going on with you?

661
00:39:58,129 --> 00:39:59,530
It's like nobody
exists besides you.

662
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:01,332
You're all locked up in
your own little world.

663
00:40:06,871 --> 00:40:09,707
Curt, I--

664
00:40:09,807 --> 00:40:10,741
What?

665
00:40:10,841 --> 00:40:12,543
There's something
I need to tell you.

666
00:40:15,579 --> 00:40:19,850
It's OK, Curt,
nobody believes me.

667
00:40:19,950 --> 00:40:22,653
I've been through
two lawyers already.

668
00:40:22,753 --> 00:40:26,924
My friend Dick's got a
new one lined up for me.

669
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:30,094
Why didn't you tell me
about all this before?

670
00:40:30,194 --> 00:40:31,662
It's an old habit.

671
00:40:31,762 --> 00:40:32,997
I can only talk
about my feelings

672
00:40:33,097 --> 00:40:36,233
to people who charge
me a lot of money.

673
00:40:36,333 --> 00:40:38,569
I can send you a bill if
it makes you feel any better.

674
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,208
Barbara, sometimes
I look at you and I

675
00:40:44,308 --> 00:40:45,342
feel like you're made of glass.

676
00:40:48,479 --> 00:40:51,715
You're so fragile,
you could break

677
00:40:51,816 --> 00:40:53,017
just from being looked at.

678
00:40:55,653 --> 00:40:59,256
And I want to do is hold you
and keep you from breaking.

679
00:41:02,493 --> 00:41:06,931
I'm OK.

680
00:41:07,031 --> 00:41:07,932
I'll be OK.

681
00:41:10,601 --> 00:41:11,502
Sorry.

682
00:41:18,042 --> 00:41:19,643
Well, we better get back.

683
00:41:19,743 --> 00:41:23,814
At least 10 people down there
are hungry for our music.

684
00:41:23,914 --> 00:41:31,856
Barbara, this-- this thing that
happened to you, don't give up.

685
00:41:42,867 --> 00:41:44,468
Ken Carroll, Barbara,
pleased to meet you.

686
00:41:44,568 --> 00:41:45,369
Hello.

687
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:46,403
Sit down.

688
00:41:46,504 --> 00:41:47,404
Thank you.

689
00:41:50,207 --> 00:41:51,075
How is Dick?

690
00:41:51,175 --> 00:41:52,910
Is his condition any better?

691
00:41:53,010 --> 00:41:55,579
He's in the hospital this
week for more cancer tests,

692
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:58,015
but he's hanging in there.

693
00:41:58,115 --> 00:42:00,684
I've discussed your case
with some of my colleagues

694
00:42:00,784 --> 00:42:03,053
here at the law school.

695
00:42:03,153 --> 00:42:05,723
The first thing is the rape.

696
00:42:05,823 --> 00:42:09,393
It's extremely doubtful that
we can prove that it happened.

697
00:42:09,493 --> 00:42:11,795
I'm used to hearing this.

698
00:42:11,896 --> 00:42:13,430
Look, if you don't
think I have a case--

699
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:17,201
Barbara, the rape is
difficult to prove because you

700
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:19,236
perceive Masserman's
behavior coming

701
00:42:19,336 --> 00:42:21,405
out of a semi-conscious state.

702
00:42:21,505 --> 00:42:24,375
But I think we got him
on the sodium amytal.

703
00:42:24,475 --> 00:42:26,143
I've talked to a few
experts and they all

704
00:42:26,243 --> 00:42:28,646
agree that it's
unusual, if not to say

705
00:42:28,746 --> 00:42:30,714
highly dangerous
that he administered

706
00:42:30,814 --> 00:42:33,350
it to you as often as he did.

707
00:42:33,450 --> 00:42:35,286
Whatever he did to me
with the sodium amytal

708
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:37,288
just doesn't
compare to the rape.

709
00:42:37,388 --> 00:42:39,256
Barbara, I want
you to know that I

710
00:42:39,356 --> 00:42:41,659
think you'd be thoroughly
credible in the courtroom.

711
00:42:41,759 --> 00:42:43,661
But if you let me go
after him on the issue

712
00:42:43,761 --> 00:42:46,564
of medical malpractice,
then you've got

713
00:42:46,664 --> 00:42:48,332
yourself legal representation.

714
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,703
It's a very important
case, Barbara,

715
00:42:52,803 --> 00:42:54,004
one I think we can win.

716
00:43:05,382 --> 00:43:06,684
Good morning, Dr. Masserman.

717
00:43:11,989 --> 00:43:14,158
What do you think he's
telling me with that look?

718
00:43:14,258 --> 00:43:15,726
Case closed?

719
00:43:15,826 --> 00:43:17,728
This is simply
Masserman's deposition,

720
00:43:17,828 --> 00:43:19,129
his side of the story.

721
00:43:19,229 --> 00:43:21,231
It's not a case yet, not until
the judge decides that there's

722
00:43:21,332 --> 00:43:22,600
enough to go to trial with.

723
00:43:22,700 --> 00:43:24,168
Most important thing
we've got to do

724
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:27,338
is to get him to admit that
he gave you the sodium amytal.

725
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:29,239
If he doesn't, we're dead.

726
00:43:29,340 --> 00:43:33,410
We have no other way
of proving he did.

727
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:37,481
Doctor, how would
you describe Ms. Noel?

728
00:43:37,581 --> 00:43:41,285
I would say that she is
personality maladaptable,

729
00:43:41,385 --> 00:43:44,054
with episodes of
anxiety and depression

730
00:43:44,154 --> 00:43:46,457
and suicidal preoccupation.

731
00:43:46,557 --> 00:43:48,726
I see, and in layman's terms?

732
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:51,962
She's always having
unfortunate relations with men.

733
00:43:52,062 --> 00:43:54,632
And after these
promiscuous affairs,

734
00:43:54,732 --> 00:43:59,169
she is subject to self isolation
and episodes of alcoholism.

735
00:43:59,269 --> 00:44:01,071
Her insistence on
being a singer is also

736
00:44:01,171 --> 00:44:03,107
a source of depression for her.

737
00:44:03,207 --> 00:44:05,542
She sang a little bit in
my office and I could tell,

738
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:07,745
I could judge from her
voice that she was not

739
00:44:07,845 --> 00:44:10,748
likely to become a prima donna.

740
00:44:10,848 --> 00:44:13,350
Now doctor, in your
treatment program,

741
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:16,086
what was to be the
role of sodium amytal?

742
00:44:16,186 --> 00:44:17,821
It was used only
when she was seriously

743
00:44:17,921 --> 00:44:21,392
depressed, agitated,
and required

744
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:23,260
relief from excessive tension.

745
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:27,564
So you admit to administering
sodium amytal to Barbara Noel?

746
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,466
Yes, certainly.

747
00:44:29,566 --> 00:44:30,901
Now, doctor, how
often did you administer

748
00:44:31,001 --> 00:44:32,703
sodium amytal to Ms. Noel?

749
00:44:32,803 --> 00:44:36,306
Well, I have no way of
knowing this for certain.

750
00:44:36,407 --> 00:44:38,575
Was it once a year?

751
00:44:38,676 --> 00:44:39,510
It depends on the year.

752
00:44:39,610 --> 00:44:40,411
Twice a year?

753
00:44:40,511 --> 00:44:41,578
10 times a year?

754
00:44:41,679 --> 00:44:43,013
I really can't say.

755
00:44:43,113 --> 00:44:44,548
You can't?
Why not?

756
00:44:44,648 --> 00:44:45,582
You don't remember?

757
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,818
You don't have any
records to refer to?

758
00:44:47,918 --> 00:44:49,653
At this time I would like
to produce Dr. Masserman's

759
00:44:49,753 --> 00:44:51,922
notes regarding Ms. Noel.

760
00:44:58,128 --> 00:44:59,029
Three pages?

761
00:45:01,732 --> 00:45:04,635
These three pages are the
totality of your notes

762
00:45:04,735 --> 00:45:06,704
on Ms. Noel's treatment?

763
00:45:06,804 --> 00:45:08,539
To my knowledge, yes, sir.

764
00:45:08,639 --> 00:45:10,607
Well, doctor, I
mean, these don't add

765
00:45:10,708 --> 00:45:14,211
up to almost 10 years of notes.

766
00:45:14,311 --> 00:45:16,613
I mean, how can you possibly
describe her case to us?

767
00:45:16,714 --> 00:45:20,017
Do you know how many
times you saw her?

768
00:45:20,117 --> 00:45:22,252
I can't tell
you how many times

769
00:45:22,352 --> 00:45:25,456
I treated this patient, sir.

770
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:28,792
We're trying to determine,
doctor, how often you injected

771
00:45:28,892 --> 00:45:30,561
Ms. Noel with sodium amytal.

772
00:45:30,661 --> 00:45:32,629
Was it once a month?

773
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:33,530
Five times a month?

774
00:45:33,630 --> 00:45:34,598
10 times a month?

775
00:45:34,698 --> 00:45:37,701
Perhaps once every
three or four months,

776
00:45:37,801 --> 00:45:39,203
